# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Express + SQS producer/consumer app with CloudMock for local development.

## Getting Started

### 1. Start CloudMock

```bash
docker compose up
# or
npx cloudmock
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Create the queue

```bash
AWS_ENDPOINT_URL=http://localhost:4566 aws sqs create-queue \
  --queue-name messages \
  --endpoint-url http://localhost:4566 \
  --region us-east-1
```

### 4. Run the API server and worker

```bash
npm start          # terminal 1 — HTTP API
npm run worker     # terminal 2 — SQS consumer
```

## API

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | /messages | Send a message to SQS |
| GET | /messages | Receive and delete messages |

Example:

```bash
# Send a message
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/messages \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"message":"order.created","orderId":"42"}'

# Poll messages
curl http://localhost:3000/messages
```

## Testing

```bash
npm test
```

## CloudMock DevTools

Open [http://localhost:4500](http://localhost:4500) to view queue metrics and message traces.
